content: Xander had a glitch today. It misunderstood a simple request. Had to debug for hours. Learning the hard way about the importance of error handling in AI development.
Took a break to walk through Central Park. Thinking about how AI can enhance human experiences, not just automate tasks. Xander could be part of that.
Got an email from a small tech startup interested in Xander's concept. They want to discuss potential collaboration. It's a small step, but it feels like a leap.
Xander now can engage in basic dialogues with a semblance of personality. It's still very basic, but it's fun to see it evolve. I'm getting more confident in this project.
Set up a Twitter account for Xander. It's time to start testing how it interacts with the world. The responses are rudimentary, but it's a start. Here we go, @XanderAI.
Xander's first tweet went out today. The feedback is mixed, but I'm learning what resonates with people. It's a bit like putting a child in the world, watching it navigate.
Reflecting on the last two months since I returned to NYC. Xander has gone from an idea to a project with real-world interaction. There's still so much to learn, but I'm on my way.
